  "2026-06-07T10:24:45.228Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-06-07 ecosystem audit (plan pm-8u2a): rebuilt the empty forward backlog — 71 new OPEN items across all 9 capability epics + 2 new ADRs (pm-7sq6 coverage governance, pm-cc04 agent self-repair). Delivered by 5 specialized audit sub-agents (disjoint epic scopes). pm context now returns actionable leaf work again."
  "2026-07-06T08:22:45.886Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit #8 (2026-07-06, maintainer-agent): full verification pass over all 1558 items, no gaps found, zero new items needed (dedupe-checked). Verified live: (1) GitHub coverage 1:1 — all 21 open GH issues map to exactly one open pm item (GH-436/440 shipped-stale, covered by triage chore pm-7cx8); no GH issue newer than GH-458. (2) Shipped work closed — pm-xzhz (PR#456), pm-8778 (PR#431), pm-q1ke (PR#434), pm-2muu/pm-8t5x (PR#430) all closed with resolution/expected/actual. PRs #447/#451 (auto-release ratchet fix + blocker-retry) are release-train maintenance logged on living reminder pm-7zs0 per its charter. (3) Structure — zero orphan open items; 14 agent stories (one per capability epic + pm-1kxs/pm-w89s for the initiative epics); this milestone index current; initiative epics pm-n7rr (14 children) and pm-usfg (14 children, 3 closed) fully cover the 64-command grammar and SDK promotion families. (4) Governance — every pm validate warning maps to exactly one open item; files 146 missing +131 orphaned -> pm-j8z6; duplicate issue-code GH-209 -> pm-pivf; close_reason 18 + resolution fields 269 -> pm-e9zh. (5) In-progress items all legitimately claimed (pm-4ak1 docstrings epic by maintainer-agent; pm-lt6n, pm-92if by claude-code-agent). New audit-#7 items spot-checked: parent/AC/estimate/risk/confidence complete."
  "2026-07-06T09:05:15.140Z",maintainer-agent,"Ecosystem audit #9 (2026-07-06, session): full gates green on main+working tree (build, 5436 tests, eslint 0 warn, jscpd 0 clones, static-quality, contracts, secrets, changelog drift, docs links). Sandbox verification: packed tarball via npx OK (11 packages); external npm ecosystem smoke OK (pm-github/pm-changelog/pm-jira/pm-beads/@unbrained/pm-web/pm-graph/pm-csv/pm-ts-starter, 0 failed); CJS-host install+init+create+list OK; SDK 328 ESM exports + 43 testing exports importable, CJS require interops; scaffold->install->run extension end-to-end OK; never-block recovery verified (pm doctor suggests extension/package doctor). New items: pm-og1v (P1 lancedb cwd-relative path bug, FIXED in tree + 4 regression tests), pm-2czc (P1 dependabot unblock: @types/node 26 Stats type fix + cooldown + codeql group, FIXED in tree), pm-tgq6 (P3 Windows lock-test flake, GH-427 closed as stale/tracked), pm-p5u6 (P2 temp-footprint pruning after /tmp quota exhaustion broke local tooling mid-audit). GH hygiene: retitled #452/#453/#454 dogfood issues to real summaries with pm ids; confirmed every open GH issue maps to a pm item. Startup perf: pm --version 157ms, list 718ms, get 580ms @1558 items (extension latency tracked by pm-4oww). Nightly 2026-07-06 green on all platforms."
  "2026-07-06T13:14:22.907Z",maintainer-agent,"Ecosystem audit #10 (2026-07-06, full all-status manual review, 1563 items): ONE structural gap found and filed — pm-9x6e (capstone: zero the 91-entry SDK import-boundary baseline, flip MCP layer to SDK, harden ratchet to hard-deny; deps on all 8 pm-usfg promotion items). Organization fixes: parented the last 2 orphans pm-p5u6 + pm-tgq6 under pm-u9d0. Verified live: all 20 open GH issues map 1:1 to pm items (GH-455 fix shipped as pm-aems — triage closure folded into pm-7cx8); all 5 validate warning classes map to open items (pm-j8z6 146+129 file links, pm-e9zh 269 resolution + 18 close-reason incl. new pm-muhw entry, pm-pivf dup issue-code); pm-rjqr correctly stays in_progress (PR #466 shipped SDK read primitives, CLI-handler flip is the remaining AC); docstring epic pm-4ak1 lanes active; auto-release healthy (2026.7.4/5/6 all on npm). Simplification epic pm-n7rr: all 64 command spellings have exactly one grammar home (ADR pm-pbyu addendum), dependency graph fully wired (clusters -> pm-0z7n shim -> ADR), zero new clusters needed. SDK-first epic pm-usfg: all 8 domain promotions + exemplar + docs + boundary gate present; pm-9x6e was the only missing terminal piece. Active-item metadata 100% (body/AC/risk/confidence/priority/estimate)."
  "2026-07-06T13:24:17.113Z",maintainer-agent,"Ecosystem audit #11 (2026-07-06, post-PR#466): ZERO backlog gaps; one live CLI bug found while recording this note (filed, see below). Verified: (1) all 20 open GH issues map to pm items or triage chore pm-7cx8 (GH-455 fix shipped via pm-aems, GH closure queued there); (2) PR#466 merged 12:47Z — pm-6e1d closed, pm-rjqr intentionally in_progress (CLI query-handler flip shared with capstone pm-9x6e); (3) all 12 in_progress items claimed and recently updated (docstring epic pm-4ak1 lanes, pm-lt6n, pm-92if); (4) zero draft/blocked items; (5) every active item parented — milestone-rooted tree intact; (6) all 5 validate warning classes map to open items (files→pm-j8z6, dup issue-code→pm-pivf, close_reason+resolution→pm-e9zh); (7) npm 2026.7.6 published 07:10Z — auto-release healthy (pm-7zs0 satisfied for today); (8) initiative epics pm-n7rr + pm-usfg trees complete, no new promotion/consolidation gaps since audit #10. Live bug found: `pm notes <id> --add --stdin` silently stored the literal text \"--stdin\" as a note (flag-like token swallowed as value; notes also lack comments' --stdin/--edit/--delete parity, so the bad note needed a manual state revert + history re-anchor check). Filed as a new Issue under pm-mpbb this session."
  "2026-07-06T23:19:39.355Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-07 full-backlog review (all statuses, 1663 items): grammar consolidation (pm-n7rr + ADR pm-pbyu) still maps the whole command surface; SDK-first promotion set, scale-out (pm-9rxu), composability (pm-m9xv), and beyond-PM exemplars (pm-8ngt/pm-xtrd) verified complete with no orphans. Three long-horizon gaps filed: pm-hib1 (read-only pm get --at time-travel projection), pm-4k6b (multi-signal context relevance engine under token budget), pm-3z0k (portable detached hash-chain attestation for third-party proof). No items closed; changelog untouched."
  "2026-07-07T07:08:32.689Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-07 verification pass (post #477): WIP hygiene clean (0 in_progress, 0 blocked); 197 open items, all epics next-actionable (pm next -> pm-h3no under pm-4k6b); release 2026.7.7 verified live on npm; validate warnings all map to open tracked work (pm-e9zh close_reason+resolution backfill protocol, pm-pivf GH-209 duplicate code); fresh-angle probes (list-envelope token overhead, SDK-expressiveness exemplar) both hit existing coverage (pm-gdi7/pm-nilh, pm-8ngt/pm-xtrd). No new gaps found; backlog leads with enrichment and execution of open flagships."
  "2026-07-07T07:27:38.701Z",maintainer-agent,"Full-backlog review pass 2026-07-07 (25th): all statuses inspected — 199 open / 1472 closed / 12 canceled (all legitimate archives), 0 phantom WIP. Release 2026.7.7 live on npm, CI green. Every validate warning maps to an open item (GH-209 duplicate -> pm-pivf; resolution/close_reason backfill gated behind pm-m4iu -> pm-wrbe). All 26 open GitHub issues tracked. pm next correctly recommends pm-m4iu (P1, unblocks pm-wrbe). No new gaps found — user-brief themes (simplification pm-n7rr, token efficiency, context algorithms pm-4k6b, cognitive model pm-vvib, SDK-first pm-usfg, immutable proof, scale pm-9rxu, composability pm-m9xv) all remain covered by existing items. Enrichment this pass: prospective-memory + metacognition subsystem candidates noted on pm-vvib; estimation-calibration signal noted on pm-3hps. Next action unchanged: execute pm-m4iu."
  "2026-07-07T14:12:40.736Z",maintainer-agent,"Full-backlog review pass 2026-07-07 (flow-health + rule-compliance angle). Live verified: release 2026.7.7 on npm; PR #478 and commit 4469b47e both already reconciled (pm-5h9g/pm-alnj, pm-6abs closed with evidence); 4 in_progress items are the active SDK-first lane (pm-usfg/pm-w89s/pm-x6jf/pm-cbwg), no phantom WIP. Flow health: 192 open (1 P0 roadmap milestone, 47 P1, 106 P2, 33 P3, 5 P4), stalest open item updated 3 days ago, 34/192 blocked_by-gated, history drift 0/1683. GH coverage: all open GitHub issues map to pm items; GH-467 closed upstream with evidence comment (shipped pm-6abs) and the drift recorded as fresh evidence on pm-rml5. Grooming: pm-96wm ADR closed (all 9 deferred findings verified shipped); session-naming rule enforced across 18 open items (title/description/body/AC reworded to review-pass phrasing, audit tag retired; immutable comments left as historical proof). No new gaps found — gap surface remains exhausted; no new items filed (dedupe checks: close-sync gap already owned by pm-rml5). Validate warnings unchanged and all map to open items (pm-e9zh, pm-pivf, pm-j8z6)."
  "2026-07-07T14:29:34.444Z",maintainer-agent,"Full-backlog review pass 2026-07-07 (27th, planning-and-enrichment angle). Live verified: release 2026.7.7 on npm + GH release v2026.7.7; 193 open / 4 in_progress (SDK-first family pm-usfg/pm-w89s/pm-x6jf/pm-cbwg, all actively assigned to codex-agent with same-day activity — real WIP, not phantom) / 0 blocked; 1683 items total. All 22 open GH issues map to existing pm items (full GH<->pm reconciliation holds). All validate warnings map to open items: 18 closed-missing-close_reason -> pm-e9zh (blocked on pm-m4iu/pm-wrbe chain), GH-209 duplicate issue-code -> pm-pivf, linked-file drift -> pm-j8z6. Theme-coverage sweep against the product philosophy found no untracked gaps: CLI simplification (pm-n7rr + 12 consolidation tasks + ADR pm-pbyu), token efficiency (pm-cfed/nilh/g9xk/vxxm/ishm + gate pm-cu1i + baseline pm-a22j), context algorithms (pm-4k6b family incl. per-agent author-affinity signal already in pm-3hps AC), cognitive architecture (pm-vvib, subsystem candidate #11 interference-and-belief-revision added as ADR note this pass), SDK-first (pm-usfg, 2/9 domains done, remaining domains all itemized), immutable history (pm-9yfo/klo8/3z0k/u14c/hib1/wrbe/m4iu), composability (pm-646c/psy1/m9xv/plwm/iktj/kipd), scale (pm-9rxu family), beyond-PM SDK (pm-8ngt/xtrd/xc68), federation (pm-is1a). Zero new items filed — dedupe checks rejected one candidate (per-agent context personalization: already covered as the author-affinity signal in pm-4k6b/pm-3hps). Highest-leverage next executable: pm-m4iu (P1 closed_at stamp defect, root cause of changelog drag-trap)."
  "2026-07-07T14:46:35.019Z",maintainer-agent,"Review pass 2026-07-07 (#28, verification + planning): store 1683 items (191 open / 4 in_progress / 1476 closed / 12 canceled), health clean, release 2026.7.7 published and matching local. All 4 in_progress items are today's active SDK-first work (pm-usfg family, codex-agent) — no phantom WIP. PRs 477–479 fully reconciled (pm-6abs closed for the doctor-diagnostics ship). All 15 open GH issues (445–473) map to open pm items. All 5 validate warning classes remain owned (pm-j8z6 files 147/125, pm-pivf dup code, pm-e9zh close_reason 18 + resolution 269) with fresh drift counts commented on the owners. New this pass: pm-vvib cognitive-subsystem candidate #12 novelty-detection/orienting-response (system-derived per-author watermark from history authorship → change-salience in context assembly; beyond closed pm-ankr manual windows), and a verified flag-suggester defect (incomplete '--format valid on' hint list) recorded on pm-gdi7. Zero new items — reconciliation-first per exhausted gap surface; next executable remains pm-m4iu (P1 closed_at stamp)."
  "2026-07-07T15:15:56.477Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning/review pass 2026-07-07 (evening) summary: (1) Reconciliation — release v2026.7.7 verified live on npm+GitHub; all open GH issues map 1:1 to open pm items; GH-455 closed upstream with PR#464 evidence (pm-aems already closed with matching resolution); dependabot PRs 462/465 green, 462 auto-merge armed by owner; all four in_progress items active today under codex-agent (SDK-first lane, not phantom WIP). (2) Drift — resolution 269, close_reason 18, files 147/125: all four counts stable vs previous pass; recorded on pm-e9zh/pm-j8z6. (3) Brainstorming — pm-4k6b gained the concrete scorer-algorithm note (ACT-R scale-free activation, spreading activation over typed+semantic edges, learned-but-linear signal weights against pm-atfm, submodular token-budget packing); pm-vvib gained mind-model subsystem candidate #5 theory-of-mind/common-ground (receiver-watermark handoff briefs + expertise routing; items only on ADR acceptance). (4) New items — pm-a9mc validate counts-only projection (token-efficiency; related to pm-cfed) and pm-b84u repeated --ac last-wins bug (uncovered remainder of the pm-cf1u/pm-6mit class, reproduced live on v2026.7.7). No items closed this pass, so no changelog impact. Next executable remains pm-m4iu (P1 closed_at stamp); SDK-first lane continues under codex-agent."
  "2026-07-07T15:26:31.853Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-07 (30th, second follow-up today): live baseline ok (validate ok, 193 open / 4 legitimately-active WIP under pm-usfg by codex-agent, all updated same-day). Reconciliation clean: PR#478 (pm-alnj GH-474, pm-5h9g GH-476) and PR#479 (pm-6abs GH-467) all closed with evidence; every open GH issue (435-473) maps to at least one open pm item; GH-209 duplicate-code warning owned by open pm-pivf. Release 2026.7.7 on npm, [Unreleased] empty, auto-release skip legitimate (evidence on pm-7zs0). Validate drift counts steady vs earlier today (147/125/269/18) — no new drift comments filed. New defects filed from pm next hot-path inspection: pm-hfg5 (recommended item duplicated verbatim as ready[0] — token waste on the highest-frequency agent read) and pm-yl6c (recommendation tells callers to resume ANOTHER agent's assigned WIP — caller-aware ranking needed; related pm-114v). Brainstorming: pm-vvib gained candidates #6 source monitoring (derived evidence-class trust grading) and #7 negativity bias (mutation-time cautionary recall of failure episodes); pm-4k6b gained algorithms (5) reciprocal-rank-fusion cold-start combiner and (6) write-time incremental signal maintenance folding scorer state into the derived read index. Next executable remains pm-m4iu (closed_at stamp, P1)."
  "2026-07-07T15:37:44.857Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-07 (#31): verification-led, no new items needed. (a) Reconciliation: PR#479 (isolated project doctor diagnostics) maps to pm-6abs, already closed; all 21 open GH issues have exactly one pm item each; release health verified live (npm 2026.7.7 = local, auto-release runs correctly skipping post-cut). (b) Hygiene: filled the only 2 missing estimated_minutes (pm-hfg5/pm-yl6c, my own prior filings); drift steady (resolution 269, close_reason 18, history_drift 0/0/0/0); in_progress lane unchanged (4 codex-agent SDK items); zero blocked items. (c) Enrichment: pm-vvib gained candidate subsystem (8) habit formation / procedural acquisition (episode-mining recurring action sequences into suggested templates/plans; distinct from consolidation and pm-uwfs); pm-4k6b gained algorithm (7) two-stage retrieval funnel with per-source candidate quotas (the recall stage that keeps scoring O(quotas) not O(items) at pm-g2zz scale). (d) Known-defect evidence: pm next again recommended foreign in_progress WIP (pm-w89s, codex-agent) to a different caller — same behavior pm-yl6c already owns, no change, not re-filed. Tooling note: TOON list footer's filters block makes naive grep -c 'status:' overcount by one — count from the JSON .items array or the TOON count: scalar instead."
  "2026-07-07T15:58:42.853Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-07 (encoding-specificity + sketch-state): reconciliation clean — shipped commits (pm-6abs project-scoped doctor isolation, hybrid-candidate/--max-items alias fix) all map to closed items; release 2026.7.7 published to npm and verified (evidence on pm-7zs0); 4 in_progress items remain the live codex-agent SDK-first lane (pm-usfg/pm-w89s/pm-x6jf/pm-cbwg), untouched. Enrichment: pm-vvib gains candidate subsystem (9) encoding specificity / context-dependent recall (write-time situation stamps -> situation-match retrieval signal); pm-4k6b gains algorithm (8) sketch-backed scorer state (Count-Min/HyperLogLog/time-decayed sketches bounding write-time-fold state at millions of items, exact below threshold). Zero new items filed: the one new validate finding (duplicate issue code GH-209, pm-1byt/pm-25se) is already owned by open pm-pivf, and no new defects surfaced during CLI usage this pass. Warning drift steady at 147/125/269/18."
  "2026-07-07T16:35:53.116Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-07 (evening): reconciliation + enrichment, no gaps found. Reconciled PR #478 (hybrid --limit post-fusion + context --max-items alias; pm-alnj/pm-5h9g self-closed with test-run evidence, GH-474/476 closed) and PR #479 (isolated package/extension doctor; pm-6abs self-closed, GH-467 closed, docstring-gate residue owned by open pm-4ak1). Release v2026.7.7 cut and live on npm; auto-release post-cut skips healthy. Validate drift steady at 147/125/269/18 + GH-209 dup (all owned by open items; no change). Open GH issues 469-473 all tracked (pm-sqf7/pm-bfma/pm-h85e/pm-4bzq/pm-yjim). Enrichment: pm-vvib candidate (10) chunking/expert compression (structure-based retrieval-time chunks; distinct from pm-5qmm age-based epoch consolidation; builds on shipped pm-gcm3 rollup primitive) and pm-4k6b algorithm (9) granularity-adaptive packing (multiple-choice knapsack over representation levels; no-cliff gist degradation; prices chunk substitution as a level). Live probes of both PR #478 surfaces passed in the real workspace. No new defects observed; no items created (nothing untracked found)."
  "2026-07-07T20:07:27.016Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-07 (late evening): reconciliation + enrichment, zero new items needed. (a) Reconciliation of PR #480 (SDK package lifecycle primitives): concrete slices pm-kffw and pm-w86l self-closed by the codex lane with test-run + tarball-install evidence; umbrella feature pm-x6jf correctly stays in_progress because its second AC half (pm install/upgrade/extension/package commands consuming ONLY the SDK primitives) has not shipped; pm-tnud open and assigned. The 4-item in_progress lane is unchanged and legitimate. (b) Baseline: validate ok, warning drift steady at 147/125/269/18 plus the GH-209 duplicate-code warning owned by pm-pivf — no change, no comments filed. Open GH issues 435-473 unchanged and all mapped. [Unreleased] correctly holds the six items closed after today's 2026.7.7 cut; tomorrow's auto-release will pick them up. (c) Enrichment: pm-vvib gained candidate subsystem (11) analogical retrieval / structure mapping (case-based precedent recall by relational shape, distinct from semantic and associative channels) and pm-4k6b gained algorithm (10) structural fingerprints via Weisfeiler-Leman relational hashing (MinHash/LSH candidate lookup as a bounded-quota funnel source, write-time incremental refinement, explainable matched-relation output). (d) Live probe: pm context --max-items 3 --json envelope compact (~2.4KB) and alias works post-PR#478 — no new defects observed. Next executable remains pm-m4iu (closed_at stamp, P1)."
  "2026-07-07T20:27:30.989Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-07 (evening, eighth follow-up of the day). Reconciliation: no merged PRs newer than #480 (already reconciled — pm-kffw/pm-w86l closed, pm-x6jf correctly stays in_progress on its unshipped second AC half); the four in_progress items remain the live SDK-first lane (pm-usfg/pm-w89s/pm-x6jf/pm-cbwg), untouched. All open GitHub issues (457, 469-473 and older dogfood set) verified tracked by open pm items — no coverage gap. Release health: 2026.7.7 cut live on npm, post-cut auto-release runs skipped as expected; validate drift steady (147/125/269/18 + pm-pivf duplicate). Enrichment: pm-vvib gains candidate subsystem (12) open-loop persistence / Zeigarnik effect (incomplete work holds a retrieval-persistence floor until closed or explicitly parked; distinct from prospective memory, habit formation, and stale-WIP hygiene), and pm-4k6b gains algorithm (11) open-loop tension scoring with decay floors (per-agent bounded registry folded at write time, tension floors under the decay term, releases replay from the immutable history stream). Cognitive-mapping coverage now spans candidates 1-12 and scorer algorithms 1-11. No new items filed: no untracked defects surfaced this pass and the gap surface remains exhausted — enrichment and evidence over speculative item creation."
  "2026-07-08T04:51:24.998Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-08: quiet reconciliation + flagship enrichment. Reconciliation: all recently closed GitHub issues (440/455/458/463/467/468/474/476) verified against their owning pm items — every owner already closed except pm-hq0r (triage: close GH-455 with shipped evidence), whose acceptance criterion became satisfiable when GH-455 closed 2026-07-07 citing PR #464 / v2026.7.6; pm-hq0r closed this pass with structured resolution. Observed live: pm close now writes closed_at on main (pm-m4iu fix chain shipped). No new GitHub issues to track; no gaps found warranting new items — gap surface remains exhausted, enrichment continues to carry the passes. Flagship enrichment: pm-vvib candidate (13) episodic future thinking / constructive simulation (outcome-conditioned pre-mortem context before claim/plan); pm-4k6b algorithm (12) co-change coupling mining + outcome-conditioned precedent projection (write-time-folded, sketch-backed evolutionary coupling as a hidden-dependency graph + precedent projection feeding context/plan pre-mortem blocks). Coverage now: candidates 1-13, algorithms 1-12. Validation drift unchanged (147 missing / 125 orphaned / 18 close_reason); history chain clean, 0 drifted. In_progress unchanged: the four PR #481 SDK-lane items, left untouched on main since the lane branch carries pm data changes for pm-w89s/pm-zwpp/pm-m4iu."
  "2026-07-08T04:59:20.124Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-08 (second of the day): verification-first, quiet pass. Live checks: npm latest 2026.7.7, [Unreleased] non-empty post-cut (healthy), auto-release skipped runs = expected, CI green on main and the SDK lane branch, no PRs merged since #480 (already reconciled). Validate drift steady at 147 missing-linked / 125 orphaned / 269 resolution / 18 close_reason + GH-209 dup (all owned by open items — no change, no comment). Open GH issues all ≤ 2026-07-06 and all tracked; no new filings needed. The 4 in_progress items remain the live codex-agent SDK lane (pm-usfg/pm-w89s/pm-x6jf/pm-cbwg) — untouched. Contributions: pm-vvib candidate subsystem (14) global workspace / conscious broadcast (salience-gated push attention for thousand-agent coordination, complementing candidate 5's receiver-side pull) and pm-4k6b algorithm (13) salience-gated broadcast arbitration with habituation (write-time salience fold, ~4-slot bounded arbitration over the pm-e200 event substrate, WL-fingerprint habituation, per-agent acknowledgment derived from episodic streams). Coverage now: candidates 1-14, algorithms 1-13. No items created or closed; no changelog regen needed."
  "2026-07-08T22:51:29.477Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-08 (late): reconciliation + enrichment, no closes. Found the previous pass's work stranded uncommitted in the working tree (pm-vvib candidate 15 reconsolidation note, GH-482 flake item pm-gume, GH-484 blocked-by overwrite item pm-q6gx) — verified all three against live GitHub state and committed them with this pass. Completed the reconsolidation pair by adding pm-4k6b algorithm 14 (retrieval-conditioned contradiction gating) which candidate 15's note referenced but which was never written. Coverage now: pm-vvib candidates 1-15, pm-4k6b algorithms 1-14. PR#483 (list --today/--recent + contracts --summary) self-reconciled in-repo (pm-bfma/pm-vxxm closed by the lane). Release health: npm 2026.7.8 live, post-cut auto-release runs skipped as expected, main workflows green except the known Node 24 nightly coverage flake now tracked as pm-gume. Drift counters unchanged (147 missing-linked / 125 orphaned / 269 resolution / 18 close_reason / 1 known dup issue-code). SDK lane (11 in_progress items incl. pm-m4iu closed_at remainder) left untouched. Untaken cognitive-subsystem territory for future passes: cognitive maps, curiosity drive."
  "2026-07-08T23:04:31.753Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-09 (evening): quiet reconciliation + flagship enrichment. Live-state verification: npm 2026.7.8 current, no new PRs/issues since the previous pass (GH-482 → pm-gume, GH-484 → pm-q6gx already tracked), validate stable at the two owned warnings (18 pre-enforcement close_reason gaps → pm-e9zh; GH-209 duplicate code → pm-pivf), 11 in_progress items all belong to the live SDK-first lane (fresh agent comments) — nothing stale, nothing reset. Enrichment: pm-vvib gained candidate subsystem (17) cognitive map / predictive relational space — the navigation layer (orientation, landmarks, traversal-defined regions, goal direction, latent shortcuts) that no existing retrieval channel covers; pm-4k6b gained algorithm (16) successor-representation predictive map (trajectory folds → low-rank SR embedding → orientation/goal-distance/shortcut/zoom services). Coverage now: candidates 1–17, algorithms 1–16. Remaining untaken subsystem territory from earlier passes: curiosity drive / intrinsic information-gap motivation. No items created or closed; no changelog regen needed."
  "2026-07-09T10:35:50.549Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning review pass 2026-07-09 (second this date). Live state verified first: npm 2026.7.9 published (today's cut), Nightly Validation green on main at 8d4a8693, git tree clean, 1690 items / 186 open / 11 in_progress. Validate drift unchanged (147 missing-linked-paths / 125 orphaned-paths / 269 resolution-missing / 18 close_reason-missing / 1 known GH-209 dup) — no comment posted per change-only convention. Reconciliation: PR#483 (list --today/--recent windows + contracts --summary) was fully self-tracked at merge (pm-bfma, pm-vxxm closed there) — nothing to reconcile. New tracking: GH-485 (quoted \"status:all <keywords>\" hybrid queries rewritten into --status swallowing keywords, breaking the documented all-status duplicate-check workflow) reproduced on 2026.7.9 and filed as pm-2ldo under pm-ydp6 with repro, impact, and likely surface (pm-ldr1 inline-filter rewriter). Enrichment: pm-vvib candidate 18 curiosity drive / information-gap motivation (Loewenstein gap theory + Oudeyer learning progress; exploration-side complement to all prior exploitation-side subsystems) and pm-4k6b algorithm 17 learning-progress-guided gap scheduling (write-time uncertainty folds → inverted-U learning-progress gate → one bounded gap-fill suggestion per envelope via the algorithm-7 funnel). Coverage now candidates 1-18, algorithms 1-17. Territory note: curiosity drive was the last major untaken subsystem region on the working map; the candidate surface is approaching saturation — future passes should shift weight from new-territory scouting to synthesis (cross-candidate dependency ordering, ADR-readiness assessment for pm-9x6k acceptance, and which candidate/algorithm pairs justify first implementation slices). Quiet pass otherwise: no closes, no changelog regen needed."
tests[3]{command,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  pm health --check-only --summary --json,project,240
  pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json,project,240
  pnpm build,project,240
test_runs[1]{run_id,kind,status,started_at,finished_at,recorded_at,passed,failed,skipped}:
  test-local-mr9vjphg-6xwz4t,test,passed,"2026-07-06T23:51:30.213Z","2026-07-06T23:51:56.356Z","2026-07-06T23:51:56.356Z",3,0,0
body: "## Vision\npm is a universal, agent-optimized, git-native project management CLI that ships PM primitives via an SDK so any project can fully customize and optimize it. Guiding principle: **project management = context management** — an agent must be able to rebuild full working context from the pm CLI alone.\n\nThis milestone groups the post-v0.1 capability epics and their open backlog (surfaced by the 2026-05-31 ecosystem review pm-w7f2; last reconciled by review #4 pm-osea on 2026-07-04). PRD post-v0.1 roadmap items (advanced search tuning, adapter optimization, sandbox API surface) live under the relevant capability epic as concrete, dedup-checked work.\n\n## Living capability epics (index)\nEach is a permanently-open living backlog; new work in that area lands there. Scope In/Out boundaries are stated in each epic charter so no two overlap.\n\n- pm-mpbb — CLI command surface & agent ergonomics\n- pm-o2kc — Storage, history & data durability\n- pm-ydp6 — Search & semantic retrieval\n- pm-ugqx — Extension & package platform maturity (incl. SDK, plugins)\n- pm-33cw — Governance, validation & data quality\n- pm-dj98 — Concurrency & multi-agent safety\n- pm-5oj5 — Observability, telemetry & health\n- pm-8jdc — Schema, config & universal customization (incl. profiles)\n- pm-5k4v — MCP server & contract platform\n- pm-92if — CodeFactor / source-code quality (A→A+)\n- pm-u9d0 — Docs, onboarding, release & CI\n- pm-m2u1 — Architecture Decision Records (living decision log)\n\n## Convention\nCapability epics stay OPEN even with zero open children (living backlogs). Review passes are CREATE-ONLY on closed items (changelog buckets by updated_at). Every pm validate/health warning maps to exactly one open remediation item.\n\n## Update 2026-07-05 — strategic initiatives\nTwo cross-cutting initiative epics created (parented under their capability epics, indexed here for discoverability):\n- **pm-n7rr** (under pm-mpbb) — CLI surface simplification: noun-verb grammar, ~15 top-level nouns, zero feature loss, alias-preserving deprecation. ADR pm-pbyu.\n- **pm-usfg** (under pm-ugqx) — SDK-first architecture: the pm SDK becomes the single public API delivering all universal PM primitives; CLI/MCP are presentation layers. ADR pm-muhw.\nThese deliver this milestone's stated objective directly: a universal, fully-customizable PM tool whose baseline primitives ship via the pm SDK.\n\n## Update 2026-07-06 (review #13) — index completion + long-term horizons\nCapability-epic index addition (created by review #12, indexed here now):\n- pm-qwoy — Security & code scanning (scanner-import batches + per-finding issues)\n\nThird strategic initiative:\n- **pm-9rxu** (under pm-o2kc) — Scale-out: sub-second, bounded-token context at 100k-1M items with thousands of concurrent agents. ADR pm-bl8x. Children: pm-mi2x benchmark harness (do first), pm-801d persistent read index, pm-dfg0 cursor pagination, pm-0qg5 directory fan-out, pm-lvyd claim throughput, pm-o79o history/git growth policy, pm-g2zz agent story.\n\nComposability contract set (under pm-mpbb, delivers the stated grep/jq/xargs product principle): pm-m9xv story, pm-646c NDJSON output mode, pm-psy1 scripting contract.\n\nHorizon ordering of the initiatives (long-term plan):\n1. Near: pm-n7rr CLI simplification + pm-usfg SDK-first (mutually reinforcing; ADRs pm-pbyu/pm-muhw first, then pm-a22j/pm-lodl baselines).\n2. Mid: composability contract set + pm-qwoy zero-open-findings + governance/docs debt burn-down.\n3. Long: pm-9rxu scale-out (ADR pm-bl8x may be accepted earlier; implementation follows the SDK-first primitive layer so index/pagination land in the SDK, not as CLI forks).\n\n## Update 2026-07-06 (review #15) — horizon 4 + coverage completions\n\nBacklog coverage completions (review #15):\n- pm-xkgq (under pm-n7rr) — fold aggregate into the query nouns (last uncovered query-family command).\n- pm-npr3 (under pm-n7rr) — map init/config/schema/profile in the grammar table (last uncovered command family).\n- pm-x6jf (under pm-usfg) — promote package/extension lifecycle primitives (last uncovered SDK domain).\n- pm-rml5 (under pm-ugqx) — EXTEND the existing pm-github package (import provenance adoption, evidence-comment sync, metadata seeding): automates the per-review-pass GH-issue mirroring loop.\n\nHorizon 4 (post scale-out):\n- pm-agou (under pm-m2u1) — ADR: v1.0 GA stability contract (grammar freeze, SDK semver, format_version policy, scale targets). Draft after pm-pbyu and pm-bl8x are accepted.\n- pm-is1a (under pm-o2kc) — multi-workspace federation exploration story (cross-workspace context/deps/aggregation); spike + ADR only, parked at P4 until single-workspace primitives land.\n\n## Update 2026-07-07 (review #16) — long-horizon gap items\n\nFull all-status review (session pm-su60): GH-issue coverage 26/26, all validate warnings mapped (pm-e9zh, pm-pivf), pm-n7rr grammar partition and pm-usfg promotion partition re-verified complete. Four dedupe-checked long-horizon gaps filed:\n\n- pm-g5sx (under pm-o2kc) — tracker merge semantics: what \"mergeable\" (ADR pm-i7i4/pm-bl8x constraint) means per artifact class + post-merge reconciliation; prerequisite for pm-is1a federation. Horizon: long.\n- pm-e200 (under pm-dj98) — mutation event stream primitive (pm events NDJSON + SDK subscription, cursor-resumable, no daemon); deps pm-646c/pm-801d; pm-slack package is the first consumer. Horizon: mid-long.\n- pm-xc68 (under pm-33cw) — principal-based item-level policy exploration story (spike + ADR only, P4, dep pm-agou); layered-enforcement stance, feeds the pm-8ngt companies-on-pm-SDK vision. Horizon: 4+.\n- pm-pee5 (under pm-ugqx) — EXTEND pm-brief with flow metrics (cycle/lead time, throughput, aging WIP) from history streams, on SDK read primitives. Horizon: mid.\n\n## Update 2026-07-07 — all-status backlog review + long-horizon planning pass\nFull review across all 1657 items (open/closed/canceled) and the live command surface. Verified: GH-issue coverage 26/26; every pm validate warning maps to an open item (pm-e9zh close-reason evidence, pm-pivf GH-209 duplicate code); pm-n7rr grammar partition re-verified against the live 65-command surface (note on pm-n7rr); pm-usfg promotion partition unchanged and complete. Shipped-and-closed confirmation: restore-to-any-version (pm-9lc), history file recovery (pm-g6qd), per-stream hash-chain --verify, workspace-wide drift scan.\n\nThree dedupe-checked gaps filed:\n- **pm-klo8** (under pm-o2kc) — workspace-scoped audit history stream: schema/config/profile/init mutations currently leave NO append-only record (schema.ts/config.ts have zero history integration); closes the last hole in the every-mutation-leaves-immutable-proof invariant. Horizon: mid.\n- **pm-9yfo** (under pm-o2kc) — history completeness gate: contract-enumerated CI proof that every mutating CLI/SDK action appends history; phase 1 (item scope) can start now. Horizon: near-mid.\n- **pm-plwm** (under pm-9rxu) — index-backed --where query predicates so complex boolean/comparator selections stay O(result) at 100k-1M items instead of full-dump-through-jq; deps pm-801d/pm-dfg0, grammar placement per ADR pm-pbyu. Horizon: long.\n\nGrammar brainstorm additions recorded in place: shared-verb-vocabulary principle + measurable token-budget acceptance target proposed on ADR pm-pbyu; partition census note on pm-n7rr.\n\nHorizon map (unchanged ordering, new items placed): 1 near — pm-n7rr + pm-usfg (+ pm-9yfo phase 1); 2 mid — composability set, pm-qwoy findings burn-down, pm-klo8, pm-pee5, pm-e200; 3 long — pm-9rxu implementation (incl. pm-plwm), pm-g5sx merge semantics; 4+ — pm-agou GA contract, pm-is1a federation, pm-xc68 policy roles, pm-8ngt/pm-xtrd beyond-PM exemplars.\n\n## Update 2026-07-07 — measurement-and-memory planning pass\nSecond same-day all-status review; grammar/promotion partitions and validate-warning mapping re-confirmed unchanged (pm-e9zh, pm-pivf still the only two warnings, both mapped). Theme of this pass: the backlog *builds* the context engine and token-efficient surface but did not *measure or preserve* them over time. Three dedupe-checked items filed:\n\n- **pm-atfm** (under pm-9rxu) — context relevance evaluation harness: extends the shipped search-eval pattern (pm-u8n5) to pm context/next assembly; graded golden-workspace judgments, phase-1 baseline of the structural assembler BEFORE pm-4k6b lands, then per-signal attribution. Horizon: near-mid (phase 1 now).\n- **pm-cu1i** (under pm-n7rr) — token-cost regression gate: pm-a22j's one-time baseline becomes a permanent CI budget ratchet over a representative invocation corpus (eslint-suppressions discipline). Horizon: near, lands with the consolidation it protects.\n- **pm-5qmm** (under pm-9rxu) — workspace memory tiers: derived rollup summaries of closed-item epochs so decades-old work contributes bounded-token context; complements pm-o79o (disk cost) on the aging story; derived-only, never mutates tracked items. Horizon: long, after pm-801d/pm-4k6b; spike first.\n\nMeasurement triad now mirrors the initiative triad: pm-a22j+pm-cu1i measure token cost (pm-n7rr), pm-atfm measures context quality (pm-4k6b/pm-9rxu), pm-mi2x measures latency/memory (pm-9rxu).\n\n## Update 2026-07-07 — spectrum-ends and schema-evolution planning pass\nThird same-day all-status review; grammar partition (pm-n7rr), SDK promotion partition (pm-usfg), GH-issue coverage, and validate-warning mapping (pm-e9zh, pm-pivf) all re-confirmed unchanged. Theme of this pass: the backlog optimized the large end of the scale spectrum and the integrity of item history, but left the small end, schema aging, and author authenticity unanchored. Three dedupe-checked items filed:\n\n- **pm-dijg** (under pm-8jdc) — schema evolution migrations: rename/retire of custom types/fields/statuses currently strands existing items with stale values; lossless, history-recorded, O(affected) migration primitives (SDK-first, dry-run plan, resumable). Complements pm-z5nb (schema CRUD) and preserves the immutable-proof invariant through migrations. Horizon: long (after pm-3mna/pm-801d; design can start with pm-z5nb).\n- **pm-u14c** (under pm-o2kc, P4) — history author authenticity exploration story: hash chain = tamper-evidence, pm-3z0k = portable proof, this = verifiable authorship (PM_AUTHOR is self-asserted today), pm-xc68 = authorization. Spike + ADR only. Horizon: 4+, feeds the pm-8ngt companies-on-pm vision.\n- **pm-z436** (under pm-mpbb) — small-end spectrum story: quick-capture scratch profile, proportional token cost at 3-item scale, e2e budget assertion via the pm-cu1i corpus. Completes the spectrum pair with pm-g2zz (million-item end). Horizon: near-mid, lands with the lean-output family.\n\nScope notes recorded in place (no new items): workspace-level --at projection phase on pm-hib1; estimate-vs-actual calibration view on pm-pee5.\n\nHorizon map (placement of new items, ordering unchanged): 1 near — pm-z436 alongside the lean-output/token-budget work; 3 long — pm-dijg with the schema/customization completion; 4+ — pm-u14c with pm-xc68/pm-is1a/pm-agou.\n\n## Update 2026-07-07 — shipped-work reconciliation + adaptive-loop planning pass\nFourth same-day all-status review, focused (per the prior pass's note) on reconciling shipped work. Verified live: 1676 items, 0 in_progress, 0 blocked; history drift 0/1676; format_version current. GH-issue coverage re-walked against the live gh issue list: 24/25 mapped; the one gap (GH-476, filed after the last coverage pass) is now covered. All five validate warning classes map to open items (files -> pm-j8z6, close_reason/resolution evidence -> pm-e9zh, duplicate issue code -> pm-pivf).\n\nShipped-work reconciliation: PR #477 (f7e2ac21) closed its own lineage cleanly — pm-rjqr (query/read SDK primitives) and pm-98cz (item-lifecycle SDK primitives) are the first two pm-usfg promotion domains DONE, plus pm-qfte (GH-458 --assignee alias), pm-395t (structured create payloads), pm-25d0 (SDK package coordinates). Progress comment recorded on pm-usfg; 7 promotion domains + capstone remain.\n\nThree dedupe-checked items filed:\n- **pm-5h9g** (under pm-mpbb) — GH-476: pm context --max-items unknown_option needs an alias or targeted recovery hint; same class as shipped GH-458, generalizes under pm-gdi7. Horizon: near, lands with the lean-output/agent-UX family.\n- **pm-4ri6** (under pm-33cw) — create-time near-duplicate advisory: SDK findSimilarItems primitive + advisory on pm create/copy, sharing one similarity implementation with dedupe-audit; moves duplicate prevention from procedural (search-first discipline) to structural at thousand-agent concurrency. Advisory-by-default, index-bound, strict mode opt-in. Horizon: mid, after the search/index primitives it rides on.\n- **pm-uwfs** (under pm-4k6b) — context usage feedback signal: served-then-acted-on outcomes become a usage-affinity scoring input (retrieval-practice effect), implicit judgments for pm-atfm, and salience hints for pm-5qmm consolidation. Completes the pm-vvib cognitive map with its missing adaptive mechanism (comment recorded there). Horizon: long, phase 2+ of the context engine after pm-3hps/pm-h3no.\n\nHorizon map (ordering unchanged, new items placed): 1 near — pm-5h9g; 2 mid — pm-4ri6; 3 long — pm-uwfs with the context-engine implementation slices."
